cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about a distributed file system and its performance on a cluster.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a file system and its integration with non-volatile memory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the cache coherence protocol used in the file system.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of non-volatile memory in the file system.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the failover time and consistency semantics of the file system.
